# GETKINETIK positioning

## What we are

- Independent **neutral DePIN bureau** — public Genesis Score + signed device evidence
- **Not** an earnings aggregator pitch, **not** a token project, **not** taking equity in graded networks
- Hardware-sealed Ed25519 identity per device; public verifier; partner API at `/api/verify-device`
- Genesis Score is 0–1000, methodology-published; v1.1+ uses bureau-bounded chain age

## Voice lanes (do not mix)

| Lane | Account | Job | Win metric |
|------|---------|-----|------------|
| Bureau / signal | @kinetiksignal | Daily DePIN index cards, neutral data | Reach on cards |
| Personal visibility | @Kinetik_Rick (@Ricolax310) | Builder voice, replies on big threads | Profile clicks + follows |
| Partner outreach | DMs / email | Sybil reports, bureau pitch | Warm reply → call |

Rick lane rules: replies have **no links**; max **one link post per week**; sound like a builder, not a brand bot. Partner wait-list rules in `scripts/bureau/gtm-context.md` still apply.

## Copy guardrails

- Never promise token boosts, NODL boosts, or "credits" as partner value — use **Genesis Score**, **verify-device**, **attestation**, **Sybil reads**
- Be honest on continuity: phone loss = seniority loss until backup ships
- Bureau findings must cite **public endpoints only** — "we publish what the API returns"
- Outreach: human tone, concrete numbers, no cold-AI walls of text

## Build priorities (when advising the user)

Distribution and partner replies beat infra polish until engagement exists. Prefer: Rick visibility, Sybil report outreach, landing/bureau front door, Android/iOS parity. Deprioritize: RAG/eval harnesses, dataset versioning, feature depth with no reader.

